<br>
Kendrick ya wrong about perceived value of monks and hybrids.  the high end game has really fizzled to melee absorption, melee damage, mana efficient healing, crowd control.  there's specific classes for each and all the rest are situationally better, but none are more important than those core 4.  nothing that Verant could do to the way XP is gained can change that ultimate truth.  Of the 4 classes that fill those roles, 2 have xp bonuses, one had no bonus/no penalty and one had a penalty.  I'm not bitching, I'm not whining (i don't intend to be at least), I'm just being realistic.  The XP change is nice but it's not like people all of a sudden were gonna drop their primary Rogue/Warrior and start Paladins/SKs/Monks because they are so much cooler now that they level faster.  I've never seen anyone bitch about Hybrid stealing experience since I was about level 18, most people didn't think it mattered, you needed a tank you get a tank, and at those levels, a magician/necro was as good as any other even hybrids.<br>
<br>
I know Kendrick's role in Rogue-land, and have utmost respect for his work, but I disagree with him on this small point.  Gain/Loss XP speed is a marginal issue once we know what the real values were it didn't really matter, you picked the class you want to play based on your preferences.  Maybe there will be more Troll SKs now, but somehow I doubt it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvestas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vestas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/01 9:25:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2014.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JUST in from Aradune!!!!</span><hr size=1> I don't play a hybrid, however, several members of my guild are Paladins or Rangers.   I will just state that they personally were overjoyed by this change.  These are folks who have consistently been outleveld by their rogue and warrior friends, fought longer and harder for what they believed was less benefit.<br>
<br>
Now that the change is in place, many of them are realizing the direct benefits of this change. More exp earned per night of playing.  I will add that I too, as a rogue, have seen a dramatic (i.e. noticeable) difference in the amount of exp I earn in places I fight in over the same amount of time. Likewise, lower level members in higher level parties are now seeing better returns. This makes grouping with your higher level friends less painful.  All in all, the change was a big improvement in realized experience.<br>
<br>
That change has brought some of the fun back to the hybrids in my guild and given some of them new hope in leveling again.  That in itself is good enough for me.  As for me personally, with the proper tactics, I can use just about any class in the game in my group.  This belief that enchanters and clerics are a must is just bogus. You haven't lived till you've fought in a tough dungeon, and lived, without a single enchanter or cleric in your group. (you also are missing out on some of the best challenges and most exciting times) <p><img src = "http://www.geocities.com/maxfields_2000/sunglassvest1.jpg" >

